{
  "texts": [
    "They are zero-shot learners, i.e., they can solve downstream tasks for which they have not been trained (e.g., cancer subtyping).",
    "However, due to their limitations, they cannot generate a textual description of the input image.",
    "Generative vision language models such as Med-PaLM M 14, LLaVA-Med 15, or PathChat 16 can output text, but only at the patch level for small image regions up to 1024 × 1024 pixels.",
    "Thus, none of the existing medical foundation models can generate reports from an entire pathology image at full resolution, let alone from multiple images simultaneously, e.g., from a serial section.",
    "To fill this gap, we present HistoGPT, a vision language model that can generate histopathology reports from multiple gigapixel-sized WSIs."
  ]
}